Package hr.fer.zemris.java.hw04.custom.collections

Class ArrayIndexedCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • hr.fer.zemris.java.hw04.custom.collections.Collection
      • hr.fer.zemris.java.hw04.custom.collections.ArrayIndexedCollection

  • public class ArrayIndexedCollection
extends hr.fer.zemris.java.hw04.custom.collections.Collection
    Resizeable array-backed collection of objects, storage of duplicate elements is allowed, while storage of null elements is not allowed. The default capacity is 16 if not said otherwise. It is possible to add new values, remove values, get values at specific index, copy collection to an array, clear collection, etc.
    Author:
    Dorian Ivankovic

      • insert

        public void insert​(java.lang.Object value,
                   int position)
        Insert the value at the given position in the collection with average complexity O(n/2). The value at position before inserting is not replaced, all elements after position are shifted, therefore creating an empty place for the new value. If the collection is full, it's first reallocated using the double size of the current collection.
        Parameters:
        value - - value to add
        position - - position into which value is inserted
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if position is < 0 or > size NullPointerException if value is null

      • remove

        public void remove​(int index)
        Removes the element at the specified index from the collection. Elements after index are shifted one place to the left, so the element that previously was on location index+1 is now on location index,... The average complexity of this method is O(n/2).
        Parameters:
        index - - index of the element to remove
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if index is < 0 or > size-1
